               -The Cure-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ugenn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>genn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/4/01 4:32:01 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://myst.org/ithil/doh.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Pens For Inking + Markers</span><hr size=1> Well, for starters, whatever you finally end up using just making sure your ink is waterproof. Markers are a wet medium and will just make your ink bleed and look like crap if it's not waterproof.<br>
If you don't have that kind of ink you can always ink your pics and photocopy them and marker over the copies.<br>
<br>
as for markers, the main brands used are prismacolor, tria and copic. Prismas don't bleed too well, run out fast and their colours aren't pretty and bright as the other brands, but they're a lot cheaper. Copics have nice skin tones and colours but they are bloody expensive (5$ us, 7,45$ cdn). Trias are great cause they have three nibs, have replacement nibs and can be refilled (so can copic), are less expensive, and can be found more easily than copic.<br>
As for the amount of colours a set of 60 or so is usually perfect. More is cool, less is limiting, a lot more is useless and expensive (unless you make a living with using markers..).<br>
<br>
Brush pens are cool too, but they take lots of practice to get used to, just like normal brushes. Tria and Copic offer something that ressemble them I think, if you prefer to colour with that kind of brush. <p><a href="http://myst.org/ithil" target="ithilien"><img src="http://myst.org/ithil/button20.gif" border="0" alt="ithil"></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uspikescafe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SpikesCafe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.spikescafe.com/shell.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gamera</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/4/01 5:44:36 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.spikescafe.com/spikes/speedy.gif height=100 width=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Pens For Inking + Markers</span><hr size=1> Technical pens are... the ones that give a fixed width ink lines, right? Then the best ones out there that I've found are the Rapidograph Koh-I-Noors. Um, yeah. Meth knows them better than I do, though. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
